  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "It seems that vyper stores statically sized arrays with the same encoding as dynamically sized arrays: with `loc(a[i])    =   #(a) + i` (using the syntax of https://github.com/ethereum/vyper/issues/769).\r\n\r\nBut since statically sized arrays have a known size, they can just be put out in storage directly. Solidity already does this https://solidity.readthedocs.io/en/latest/miscellaneous.html#layout-of-state-variables-in-storage and it would be nice to have compatibility here",
