    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "You would be encoding these state variables directly, using the indexing algorithm that compiler has (incrementing from zero). So, it shouldn't be possible to use it to interfere with other state variables (unless you're unlucky enough to have an array big enough that it interferes with with a hashed-type indexed variable like a mapping) because you could always calculate the next index as `loc(a) + len(a)`.",
